    <fr-coverage>FR-31 (consumer wiring guide creation)</fr-coverage>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    CREATE a new guide at `docs/guides/ai-guide-consumer-wiring.md` — a maker-facing tutorial for
    wiring a new consumer of the playbook dispatch system. R7 promotes `sprk_playbookconsumer` to
    first-class; this guide is the maker entry point for the promoted model. Covers: what a consumer
    is, how to add one (ConsumerTypes.cs + sprk_playbookconsumer row + endpoint pattern), examples
    from existing 6 consumers + chat-summarize migration case study (from Wave 9 task 091).

    CRITICAL CONSTRAINT: DO NOT modify `docs/architecture/ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md`. That
    doc is owned by `chat-routing-redesign-r1` (READ-ONLY in R7). This new guide CITES it for runtime
    details but does NOT duplicate or modify it.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Documentation author + AI-platform architect. Audience: makers + AI engineers wiring a new
    consumer surface (chat window, widget, code-page, ad-hoc launcher). Tutorial style: step-by-step,
    code-snippet-heavy, worked examples, troubleshooting.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A new file `docs/guides/ai-guide-consumer-wiring.md` covering:
    1. **What is a consumer?** — short framing: a surface that invokes playbooks via the unified
       dispatch model (`IConsumerRoutingService` + `IInvokePlaybookAi`)
    2. **The 6 existing consumers** — enumerate them with brief description (citing actual current
       codebase: spaarke-ai chat, briefing widget, etc. — discover via grep in step 2 of execution)
    3. **How to wire a new consumer** — step-by-step procedure:
       - Step 1: Add the consumer's type identifier to `ConsumerTypes.cs`
       - Step 2: Add a row to `sprk_playbookconsumer` table (Dataverse), pointing at the playbook(s) to dispatch
       - Step 3: At the consumer surface, call `IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync(consumerType)` to get the playbook FK
       - Step 4: Dispatch via `IInvokePlaybookAi.InvokePlaybookAsync(playbookId, payload)`
       - Step 5: Handle the response (which is the playbook output shape)
    4. **Worked example: chat-summarize migration** (W9 case study) — show the BEFORE state (direct
       `AnalysisOrchestrationService.ExecuteAnalysisAsync` call) and AFTER state (Path A.5 via consumer
       routing). Cite Wave 9 task 091.
    5. **Troubleshooting** — common errors (consumer not registered, playbook not found, payload
       schema mismatch) + how to debug.
    6. **Cross-references**:
       - `docs/architecture/ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md` for runtime details (READ-ONLY pointer)
       - spec FR-17 + FR-18 + FR-31
       - CLAUDE.md §10 BFF Hygiene
       - PLAYBOOK-AUTHOR-GUIDE.md (for authoring the playbook the consumer will dispatch)

    EXPLICIT EXCLUSION: This guide does NOT modify `ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md`. It cites
    that doc but does NOT duplicate runtime mechanics (cache TTL, internal classes, etc.). If the
    maker needs runtime depth, the cross-reference takes them there.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="readonly-canonical">docs/architecture/ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md (READ-ONLY in R7)</file>
    <file purpose="consumer-types">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ConsumerTypes.cs (or equivalent)</file>
    <file purpose="consumer-routing-service">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/IConsumerRoutingService.cs (interface)</file>
    <file purpose="invoke-playbook-ai">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/IInvokePlaybookAi.cs (interface)</file>
    <file purpose="w9-migration">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs (post-task-091 chat-summarize migration)</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-31">CREATE the consumer-wiring guide as R7 deliverable. Maker-facing tutorial.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-08">No SUPERSEDED markers; pure CREATE (no parallel content to existing docs).</constraint>
    <constraint source="scope-boundary STRICT">DO NOT modify `docs/architecture/ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md`. That doc is owned by chat-routing-redesign-r1 follow-on. This new guide CITES it.</constraint>
    <constraint source="scope-boundary STRICT">DO NOT create `docs/data-model/sprk_playbookconsumer.md`. That doc is owned by chat-routing-redesign-r1 follow-on.</constraint>
    <constraint source="dependency">Task 091 (chat-summarize migration) must have shipped — the worked example references actual code. If 091 hasn't shipped, scaffold the example based on FR-17 intent + note the caveat that this section will need refinement after 091 ships.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">Cost-of-doing-nothing: makers wiring a new consumer have no entry-point doc; they reverse-engineer from chat-summarize / briefing-widget code. Each new consumer reinvents the integration pattern.</constraint>
    <constraint source="LENGTH">Target 200-350 lines. Tutorial-depth, not architecture-depth. Step-by-step, examples-heavy.</constraint>
    <constraint source="audience">Audience is a maker who has NOT read the architecture doc. Use plain language. Code snippets are the load-bearing teaching tool, not prose.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>documentation</topic>
    <files>
      <file>docs/architecture/ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md</file>
