      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Pre-R7, `sprk_playbookconsumer` existed but was lightly used; consumer wiring was ad-hoc per
      surface (chat-summarize used direct `ExecuteAnalysisAsync`; briefing used /narrate-specific
      paths). R7 promotes the consumer model to first-class: every surface dispatches through
      `IConsumerRoutingService` + `IInvokePlaybookAi`. The runtime mechanics are documented in
      `docs/architecture/ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md` (READ-ONLY here). What's MISSING is a
      maker-facing tutorial for "I have a new surface and want to wire it" — this guide fills that gap.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="091" status="not-started-but-required">chat-summarize migration to Path A.5 — the worked-example case study.</dependency>
      <dependency task="064" status="not-started-but-helpful">Constraint §G update — guide cross-references it.</dependency>
      <dependency task="066" status="not-started-but-helpful">PLAYBOOK-AUTHOR-GUIDE update — guide cross-references it.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 068 may update root CLAUDE.md if this new doc warrants an entry in §17 Pointers.</item>
      <item>Task 069 post-audit verifies no SUPERSEDED markers in `docs/` after this guide is added.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: STANDARD · 📋 REASON: docs CREATE task (no .cs / .ts / .tsx / .ps1 modification, tag docs only) · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md FR-17 + FR-18 + FR-31 + (READ-ONLY) ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md + (if shipped) chat-summarize migration from task 091.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Discover existing consumers">
      Grep BFF source for `ConsumerTypes` / `IConsumerRoutingService` / `sprk_playbookconsumer`. Enumerate the 6 existing consumers in the codebase. Capture each consumer's identifier + brief purpose for the "6 existing consumers" section.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Locate ConsumerTypes.cs + relevant interfaces">
      Find `ConsumerTypes.cs` (or equivalent). Read `IConsumerRoutingService` and `IInvokePlaybookAi` interfaces. Capture exact method signatures for the step-by-step procedure section.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Identify chat-summarize BEFORE state">
      Read the pre-task-091 state of SessionSummarizeOrchestrator (or grep git log). Capture the BEFORE snippet — direct `ExecuteAnalysisAsync` call — for the worked example.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Identify chat-summarize AFTER state">
      If task 091 has shipped, read the post-migration code from ChatEndpoints.cs / SessionSummarizeOrchestrator. Capture the AFTER snippet — Path A.5 via `IConsumerRoutingService` + `IInvokePlaybookAi`. If 091 hasn't shipped, scaffold the snippet from spec FR-17 intent.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Draft the guide">
      Create `docs/guides/ai-guide-consumer-wiring.md`. Structure:
      - **§1. What is a consumer?** — short framing paragraph + 1-line definition
      - **§2. The 6 existing consumers** — table or bulleted list with consumer identifier + 1-line description
      - **§3. How to wire a new consumer** — step-by-step procedure (5 steps as enumerated in goal)
        - Step 1: ConsumerTypes.cs (code snippet)
        - Step 2: sprk_playbookconsumer row (Dataverse Web API snippet or PAC CLI snippet)
        - Step 3: ResolveAsync call (code snippet)
        - Step 4: InvokePlaybookAsync call (code snippet)
        - Step 5: Response handling (code snippet)
      - **§4. Worked example: chat-summarize migration** (BEFORE / AFTER snippets)
      - **§5. Troubleshooting** — bulleted common errors + diagnosis
      - **§6. See also** — cross-references with explicit (READ-ONLY) note on the routing doc
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Cross-reference appropriately">
      Cite `docs/architecture/ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md` (READ-ONLY pointer) + spec FR-17 + FR-18 + FR-31 + CLAUDE.md §10 + sibling PLAYBOOK-AUTHOR-GUIDE.md.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify scope boundary">
      Confirm: this task only CREATED a new file. No modifications to `ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md` or any other file in `docs/architecture/`. No new file in `docs/data-model/`.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify NFR-08 discipline">
      Grep new doc for "SUPERSEDED", "deprecated". Zero instances. Discipline: CREATE clean.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Verify guide reads coherently">
      Read end-to-end as a maker wiring a new consumer. Could they wire a working consumer from this guide alone? Code snippets must compile when copy-pasted. If not, tighten.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 067 status complete; advance current-task.md to next pending Wave 6 task.
    </step>
    <step order="12" name="Commit">
      Commit `docs/guides/ai-guide-consumer-wiring.md` with conventional message.
      Example: docs(guides/r7): create ai-guide-consumer-wiring maker tutorial (Wave 6 task 067, FR-31)
    </step>
  </steps>

